body: To get a more accurate measurement, I would suggest only measuring the duration of session.run(). The InferenceSession initialization is expected to take some time.

@Reborn-liang, you can follow the notebook:
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/onnxruntime/python/tools/transformers/notebooks/PyTorch_Bert-Squad_OnnxRuntime_CPU.ipynb

Please use optimizer tool (in section 5). Optimized node counters are like {'EmbedLayerNormalization': 1, 'Attention': 12, 'Gelu': 0, 'FastGelu': 0, 'BiasGelu': 12, 'LayerNormalization': 0, 'SkipLayerNormalization': 24} for 12 layer BERT model.

You might use older version of transformers (4.5~4.8). I think the tool need some update for latest version of transformers.

@eborn-liang, 
>how to use the optimized model?

You can use the optimized onnx model to create a session directly like
```
session = onnxruntime.InferenceSession(optimized_model_path, sess_options, providers=['CPUExecutionProvider'])
```
